result.execSummary:
The defendant Samantha A Mueller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Counterfeit Certificate of Title, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 342.32(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant Samantha A Mueller in court, in custody, with Attorney Craig M. Kuhary.  Erik J. Krueger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called for plea and sentence.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #2.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #2. Repeater enhancer is striken.  Count #1 is dismissed and read-in.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Kuhary makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant's mother makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #2:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS JAIL (STRAIGHT TIME) (CREDIT - 90 days)

TERM OF PROBATION:   2 YEARS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sign releases.
____Inform Agent of all prescriptions
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: victims listed in criminal complaint
____Criminal Thinking course
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done

RESTITUTION:  $1,070.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)

COSTS:  $268.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME:  60 Days, Non-working hours with standard release conditions - STAYED - (to be used at agent's discretion)
